Project Overview - NayePankh Foundation Internship Submission
=============================================================

Project Title: NayePankh NGO Management Portal

Internship Applied For: Full Stack Development

Objective:
To build a comprehensive full-stack NGO management web application for NayePankh
Foundation that serves as a centralized portal for managing volunteers, internship
applicants, events, certificates, notifications, and analytics. The platform
supports three user roles — Admin, Volunteer, and Intern — each with a tailored
dashboard and specific capabilities to streamline NGO operations.

Technologies Used:
- Frontend: React 18, React Router v6, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, Recharts,
  Axios, React Hot Toast, React Icons
- Backend: Node.js, Express 4, MongoDB + Mongoose, JWT Authentication, bcryptjs,
  express-validator, Multer, Nodemailer, PDFKit
- Deployment: Vercel (frontend), Render (backend API)
- Tools: Git, npm, concurrently

Features:
- Role-based authentication (Admin, Volunteer, Intern) with JWT tokens
- Password reset flow via email
- Volunteer management with approval workflow, profile completion tracking, CSV export
- Internship application system with department selection, task management, progress tracking
- Event management with CRUD, registration, capacity tracking, attendance marking
- Certificate generation with branded PDF layout, download and email delivery
- Notification system with role-targeted messages, read/unread tracking
- Analytics dashboard with charts (volunteer growth, event participation, internship stats)
- AI-powered chatbot with quick actions and conversation history
- Dark mode support with system preference detection
- Responsive design with mobile hamburger menu
- Animated UI with Framer Motion, lazy loading, skeleton states

Challenges Faced:
- Implementing complex MongoDB aggregation pipelines for analytics dashboard
  (monthly volunteer growth, popular events by registration count)
- Role-based access control across both frontend routes and backend middleware
- PDF certificate generation with custom branding layout using PDFKit
- File upload handling for resumes, cover letters, and event banners via Multer
- Deployment coordination between Vercel (static frontend) and Render (Node API)
- Ensuring responsive dark mode theming across all components

Future Improvements:
- Add real-time notifications using WebSockets (Socket.io)
- Implement payment gateway integration for donations
- Add email template system with HTML formatting
- Build a mobile app version using React Native
- Add multi-language support (Hindi + English)
- Implement data backup and export (full DB dump)
- Add OAuth login (Google, GitHub)
- Add unit and integration tests
